title: What is the biggest deficit ever overcome by Rutgers? Not 25
text:
What is the biggest deficit ever overcome by Rutgers? Not 25 Ryan Dunleavy , @rydunleavy 6:13 p.m. EDT October 18, 2015 Rutgers place kicker Kyle Federico, right, and Joey Roth celebrate after Federico kicked a 26-yard field goal as time expired to defeat Indiana 55-52 in an NCAA college football game, Saturday, Oct. 17, 2015, in Bloomington, Ind. AP Photo/Doug McSchooler) (Photo: Doug McSchooler, AP) 3 CONNECT 2 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
BLOOMINGTON, Ind. - Call it the the biggest comeback victory in Rutgers football history, but don't call it the biggest deficit overcome. 
Twice in the last eight games dating back to last season Rutgers has prevailed in a game that it trailed by as many as 25 points. 
After setting the school record for biggest comeback in the regular-season finale against Maryland last season, Rutgers matched the performance Saturday with a 55-52 win against Indiana. 
But Rutgers is going to have to dig a bigger hole if it wants to earn another place in the record book.
